---
import DocsPageShell from '../../components/DocsPageShell.astro'
import PromptCard from '../../components/PromptCard.astro'
---

<DocsPageShell
  title="Skills And Prompts"
  description="Use prompts for straightforward live questions. Use skills when you want your agent to follow a repeatable operator flow with the current local source as truth."
  eyebrow="Operator Guide"
  canonical="https://ouroboros.bot/docs/skills-and-prompts"
  intro="This page is about handoff quality. The goal is to give your agent the right amount of structure without trapping it inside stale website copy."
  noteTitle="Recommended handoff"
  noteBody="Ask your agent to start with the current skills manifest, choose the relevant skill, and inspect the latest local source before it acts."
>
  <section class="grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-2">
    <PromptCard
      prompt={`List the skills currently published for Ouroboros, tell me which one is most relevant to my task, and inspect the local install or repo before you use it.`}
      footnote="Best for discovery when you know the task but not the right handoff."
    />
    <PromptCard
      prompt={`This is my task: [replace with your task]. Decide whether a simple prompt is enough or whether you should load a matching skill first. Explain your choice before you proceed.`}
      footnote="Best for avoiding overkill when the job might not need a full skill flow."
    />
  </section>

  <section class="grid gap-5 lg:grid-cols-[0.95fr_1.05fr]">
    <div class="rounded-[26px] border border-canopy/40 bg-undergrowth/20 p-7">
      <p class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-scale/70">Prompt first when</p>
      <ul class="mt-5 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-mist">
        <li>You need a current answer to a specific question.</li>
        <li>You want your agent to inspect the live source and summarize what it finds.</li>
        <li>The task is narrow enough that structure would only slow it down.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-[26px] border border-scale/20 bg-[linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(45,148,71,0.08),rgba(5,10,7,0.9))] p-7">
      <p class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-scale/70">Use a skill when</p>
      <ul class="mt-5 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-mist">
        <li>The task has a repeatable sequence and common failure modes.</li>
        <li>You want the agent to follow a known operator flow.</li>
        <li>You still want the agent to inspect the current code or environment before acting.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsPageShell>
